# Implementation Plan - Microsoft Authentication

This plan outlines the implementation of Microsoft Authentication using an embedded WebView2 for a seamless user experience.

## Goal
Enable users to log in with their Microsoft/Minecraft accounts directly within the launcher.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This implementation requires the `Microsoft.Web.WebView2` NuGet package. I will add this dependency.

## Proposed Changes

### Dependencies
#### [MODIFY] [GeminiLauncher.csproj](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/GeminiLauncher.csproj)
- Add `Microsoft.Web.WebView2` package reference.

### Services
#### [MODIFY] [AuthenticationService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/AuthenticationService.cs)
- Implement [GetAuthorizationCodeAsync](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/AuthenticationService.cs#92-115) to support an interactive flow (using the new Dialog).
- Ensure the full OAuth -> Xbox -> XSTS -> Minecraft flow is robust.

### UI
#### [NEW] [MicrosoftLoginDialog.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/Dialogs/MicrosoftLoginDialog.xaml)
- A dialog window containing a `WebView2` control.
- Logic to listen for navigation to the redirect URI and capture the authorization code.

#### [MODIFY] [SettingsPage.xaml.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/SettingsPage.xaml.cs)
- Connect the "Add Microsoft Account" button to the new login flow.

#### [MODIFY] [AccountManager.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/AccountManager.cs)
- Update to handle the async login process and store the new Microsoft account type.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Click "Add Microsoft Account" in Settings.
2.  Verify the login dialog appears with the Microsoft login page.
3.  Log in with a real account.
4.  Verify the dialog closes automatically upon success.
5.  Verify the new account appears in the Accounts list with the correct skin/avatar.
6.  Verify launching the game uses the correct authenticated token.
